   Reder   3."]},{"name":"Redhead","meanings":["English:","nickname for someone with red hair, from Middle English <i>red</i> ‘red’ + <i>he(ve)d</i> ‘head’. Compare   Redman  .","habitational name from an unidentified place in northern England called <i>Redhead</i>, probably meaning ‘red headland’."]},{"name":"Rodman","meanings":["English: occupational name for a thatcher or reed-cutter, from Southwest Middle English <i>rod(e)</i>, <i>rud(e)</i> (Old English <i>hrēod</i>) ‘reed’ + <i>-man</i>. Synonymous with   Redman   1.","English: topographic name for someone who lived at a clearing, from Middle English <i>rode</i> (Old English <i>rodu</i>) or Southwest Middle English <i>rude</i> (Old English <i>rȳde</i>) ‘clearing’ + <i>man</i>. See   Redman   2.","Americanized form of German <b>Rodmann</b>: variant of <b>Rodemann</b> (see   Rodeman  )."]}]},{"name":"Mary","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["From Latin <i>Maria</i> via Old Welsh <i>Meir</i>.  See  <b>Mary</b> ."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"Mary Redman was born about 1405, in Yorkshire, England, United Kingdom. She had at least 3 sons with Richard Redman of Bossall. She died in Bossall, Yorkshire, England, United Kingdom."},"et":{"Abt 1405–":"umbes 1405–Surnud","1398–Male":"1398–Surnud","1435–Male":"1435–Surnud","1405–Female":"1405–Surnud","1435":"1435","1398":"1398","02 May 1435":"2. mai 1435","Abt 1405":"umbes 1405","2 May 1435":"2. mai 1435","1405":"1405",", , Yorkshire, England, United Kingdom":"Yorkshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Bossall, Yorkshire, England, United Kingdom":"Bossall, Yorkshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Bossall, Yorkshire, England":"Bossall, Yorkshire, England","Wisbeach, Cambridgeshire, England, United Kingdom":"Wisbeach, Cambridgeshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom"},"fi":{"Abt 1405–":"noin 1405–Kuollut","1398–Male":"1398–Kuollut","1435–Male":"1435–Kuollut","1405–Female":"1405–Kuollut","1435":"1435"